^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|We'll get to 2@D, 2@H and 2@S openings in a later installment of this series. For now, let's presume that 2@C (artificial) is the only suit bid to depict a strong hand. (In the old days, all 2-level openings were strong, but sanity has since prevailed.)|
PG| ***** 11 ***** |


AT|

What do I mean by "strong?" If your strong hand is balanced, I can tell you an exact point range. Presuming a 2NT opener is 20-21, then when 2@C is opened with a balanced hand it shows 22+ HCP.|
PG| ***** 12 ***** |


AT|

What if unbalanced? This is a pet peeve of mine. After an opening 2@C, an opponent asks: "How many points?" Poor question. It has no good answer. (And why ask in the first place--does it matter to you? Will you interfere or not interfere depending on the answer? By the way, if you do interfere, make sure you and your partner know what double shows--typically clubs.)|
PG| ***** 13 ***** |


AT|

Anyway, if balanced, the answer (if you are silly enough to ask what 2@C shows) is easy: more than a 2NT opener. But what about unbalanced hands? Who is to say which (if any) of the following hands are worth 2@C:|
