This hand has 17 HCP.|
pg| ***** 15 ***** |


NT||

ST||MD|1SA K J 9 6 5 4 2H-DA K 4 2C5,,,|sv|o|rh||AH|Board B|NT|^B@2
This hand has 15 HCP.|
pg| ***** 16 ***** |


NT||

ST||MD|1SK Q J T 9 8 7H-DK Q JCK Q J,,,|sv|o|rh||AH|Board C|NT|^B@2
This hand has 18 HCP.|
pg| ***** 17 ***** |


NT|^B@2 
Depending on which experts you asked, you'd get votes for opening 2@C with A (17 HCP),B (15 HCP),C (18HCP), none, or all. There is no right answer! That is why it is silly to ask your opponent: "How many points does 2@C show?"|
