cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|What should your HCP requirements be for a 2@C opener? Again, with a balanced hand, there is no decision. With unbalanced hands such as A,B,C, it is a matter of personal preference. Some people count losers or quick tricks. Others insist on having a certain number of aces or HCP. I tend to open 2@C more than most people, fearing that my one-level opening could be followed by three passes. I'd probably open 2@C with all of these hands. That doesn't make it right; many experts would open 1@S with all three hands. All of those hands are much too strong for a 4@S opening.|
PG| ***** 19 ***** |


AT|

^B@2^*BMM: And we asked Howard Schutzman'our mentor'for opinion. Next is what he said.^*N|
